#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/hanukkah.tsx:86
msgid "The festival commemorates the rededication of the Second Temple in Jerusalem."
msgstr "这一节日纪念耶路撒冷第二圣殿的重新奉献。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/diwali.tsx:123
msgid "The festival is also one of the biggest shopping seasons in India, with markets staying open late and fireworks continuing well past midnight."
msgstr "这个节日也是印度最大的购物季之一，市场营业到很晚，烟火表演延续到深夜之后。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/earth-day.tsx:143
msgid "The first Earth Day, held in 1970, grew out of environmental activism and nationwide teach-ins across the United States."
msgstr "第一届地球日于 1970 年举行，源于环保行动与美国各地的“教学活动”（teach-ins）。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/eid-al-fitr.tsx:94
msgid "The first meal of Eid, eaten after a month of fasting, carries a significance that's hard to overstate — it's often dates and something sweet, shared before the morning prayer."
msgstr "斋戒一个月后吃下的开斋节第一顿饭，其意义难以言表——通常是在晨礼前分享的椰枣和甜食。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/geminids.tsx:83
msgid "The Geminids are one of the strongest and most reliable meteor showers of the year, appearing each December with frequent, bright meteors."
msgstr "双子座流星雨（Geminids）是全年最强、也最稳定的流星雨之一，每年十二月出现，明亮流星频繁。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/eid-al-adha.tsx:71
msgid "The holiday commemorates the story of Ibrahim and his willingness to sacrifice in obedience to God."
msgstr "节日纪念易卜拉欣（Ibrahim）顺从真主、愿意献祭的故事。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/valentines.tsx:71
msgid "The holiday draws on legends of Saint Valentine and the traditions of medieval courtly love."
msgstr "这一节日源于圣瓦伦丁的传说，以及中世纪的宫廷爱情传统。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/christmas.tsx:66
msgid "The holiday we recognise today grew from early Christian tradition, layered over much older European midwinter customs tied to light, renewal, and community."
msgstr "我们今日熟悉的圣诞节，源于早期基督教传统，并叠加在更古老的欧洲仲冬习俗之上——那些习俗与光、更新与社群紧密相关。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/leonids.tsx:83
msgid "The Leonids are a November meteor shower, named for their radiant in the constellation Leo."
msgstr "狮子座流星雨是十一月的流星雨，因辐射点位于狮子座而得名。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/leonids.tsx:99
msgid "The Leonids are renowned for historic meteor storms, most notably in 1833 and 1966, when observers described the sky as seeming to rain stars."
msgstr "狮子座流星雨以历史上的“流星暴”著称，最著名的是 1833 年的一次。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/leonids.tsx:116
msgid "The Leonids originate from Comet Tempel–Tuttle, and every few decades Earth passes through especially dense streams of its debris."
msgstr "它源自坦普尔–塔特尔彗星（Tempel–Tuttle）；每隔几十年，地球会穿过更致密的碎屑流。"

#: src/features/settings/ui/initialisation.tsx:178
msgid "The location request timed out - this looks like a service issue rather than a problem on your end. Please try again in a moment."
msgstr "位置请求已超时。这看起来是服务问题，而非您设备的问题。请稍后重试。"

#: src/features/settings/ui/initialisation.tsx:186
msgid "The location request timed out. Please check your internet connection and try again."
msgstr "位置请求超时。请检查您的网络连接并重试。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/lyrids.tsx:83
msgid "The Lyrids appear each year in late April, with meteors radiating from the constellation Lyra."
msgstr "天琴座流星雨每年四月下旬出现，流星的辐射点位于天琴座（Lyra）。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/day-of-the-dead.tsx:102
msgid "The marigold paths (cempasúchil) aren't just decorative. Their strong scent is believed to guide the dead back to the living world for the night."
msgstr "万寿菊花路（cempasúchil）并非只是装饰。人们相信它们浓郁的香气能在夜晚引导逝者回到生者的世界。"

#: src/features/seasonal-events/events/earth-day.tsx:175
msgid "The math is oddly encouraging — the trees planted on Earth Day since 1970 now number in the billions."
msgstr "这些数字出乎意料地令人鼓舞——自1970年地球日以来种植的树木现已多达数十亿棵。"

